name: Coliving Bali SWEET HOME Kost Lengkap di Tabanan Kota
address: Gg. II, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1: Great place, great hospitality. Monthly cost is very reasonable considering the services and facilities provided. The host (Tania) is also very friendly, well spoken, and very helpful. The outdoor area is well maintained and clean, there's also a lot of plants that make the ambience more calm and comfortable for a long stay.
review 2:
Absolutely love this place.  Great value.  Central location.Super cute interior design. Lots of cute places to sit or hang out outside of your room.
Really friendly service.
Super clean.  Kitchen facilities.  Shop across the road with everything from food to medicine to homewares to clothing.
Stuff- great, so friendly, attentive and helpful !! We got informations to all of our questions. Restaurant recommendations, Scooter Rentals, Laundry Service, activities, tour booking, etc.
It is clean an lovely furnished.
Special THANKS to Angel hearted Tan!
review 3: This place was great! We stayed there for about a week. Our host, Tan, was fantastic. She went out of her way to help us with plans and getting around. We felt right at home :)
review 4: Incredible accommodations, clean and comfortable. Tania the host is AMAZING, extremely helpful and friendly, we had a large group and Tania was always willing to go above and beyond to work with our schedules.
review 5:
Amazing hosts and amazing location and extremely affordable.

I just stayed there for one night but they really made me feel at home!
100% recommended!

review 1: Luckily my daughter had something to attend nearby and I was hungry. After a quick search on google map this place popped up and I was a bit skeptical to try. Wow, what a surprise. Tasty, fresh sushi at an excellent price. Better than many I‚Äôve tried in the busier areas of Bali. Thank you biZakaya sushi üôèüèº
review 2:
What an amazing find! We are so happy we found this place, we are definitely coming back. The food was SO GOOD and the staff as well. Incredible atmosphere so chill and lovely. Tons of happy family and couples just enjoying themselves and good food. The food is clearly made with love and care and the presentation is amazing.

They have few vegetarian options BUT I asked the chef if he could make the Japanese curry vegetarian and we did not disappoint, it was the most amazing veggie curry I've had in a very long time. Thank you chef for being so accommodating.
review 3: The sushi taste good. Cozy place and affordable price of the menu. Recommended one is Tabanan Roll an Chuka Wakame ‚ù§Ô∏è
review 4: One of hidden gems in town. Japanese & Chinese foods specialist in Tabanan that worth a try and value for money. Premium quality and tasty food yet at very affordable price. They have wide range of Sushi roll and Sashimi. The spot features cozy and chill vibes. Suitable for all ages, small or big group and family. Attentive team and friendly owner. Tips: usually busy on the weekend so make sure to make reservation earlier for a celebration or big group‚Äôs dine in as they have limited space. Overall, it‚Äôs highly recommended. They also available on GoFood and GrabFood.
review 5: I can say this place is still a hidden gem in Tabanan. The price is insane, really cheap and the taste of the food was crazy! I really love it! I highly recommend it when you come to Tabanan. But you have to be very patient waiting for your order because it will take quite a long time.

name: Hotel Tabanan
address: Jl. Pahlawan No.10-X, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Not really marvelous due to the Melati class (supposed to be 3 star hotel), Hotel Tabanan is cheap place to spend the night. When you're late at night, feel tired, and want to lay down your body, this place is the best. However, due to the old building and only few staff, you will find it rather creepy.

Like I said, it's better to stay here for a night to rest a it. I wouldn't recommend staying here for long.

review 1: Tasty and crispy fried duck and grilled chicken. Able to customise for not having spicy sauce on top when grilling. Spacious environment. Only thing was there were flying ants in the evening attracted by the lights, but the staff had tried their best, it was just seasonal.
review 2:
I ate bebek bakar, I think this is the one of good bebek I ever eat. Well done and spicy sambal.

They prices confused me at the beginning, but they said tax excluded. Can't pay by card, only cash.
review 3: Spacious, family oriented, industrial cafe decor, reasonable prices. Simple food menu and nice fresh juice and dessert. Will go back again and even try the other branches.
review 4: I give 4 stars for this food. Their Bebek & Ayam goreng is tasty and well cooked. Their sambal also good, it just need to add on the sambal a bit more, bcos they just the small amount of sambal only above the bebek & ayam goreng. Overall is good location, in the heart of Tabanan city, nice place for hangout and eating.
review 5: I really love this place, this is my go to lunch when I was working at Tabanan General Hospital. It was right across the street. The food is great, the duck meat is so soft and the rice is fluffy. I especially love the sambal, it needs to bit a tad bit spicy to fit my liking but tastewise is amazing.

name: Warung Makan Muslim Taman Sari
address: Jl. Subali, Delod Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Nestled in the heart of Tabanan, Bali, Warung Makan Muslim Taman Sari is a hidden gem that delights the taste buds with its authentic Indonesian cuisine. Stepping into the warung, one is greeted by the warm aroma of freshly prepared dishes wafting from the kitchen, enticing diners with the promise of a satisfying meal.

The warung's menu boasts an extensive array of traditional Indonesian fare, catering to a wide range of palates. From the savory delights of nasi goreng and ayam goreng to the comforting warmth of soto and bakso, Warung Makan Muslim Taman Sari has something to tantalize every taste bud.

One of the warung's signature dishes is the nasi goreng, a symphony of flavors that perfectly captures the essence of Indonesian cuisine. The fragrant rice, stir-fried with an assortment of vegetables, meat, and eggs, is a testament to the warung's culinary expertise. Each bite is an explosion of taste, with the interplay of savory, sweet, and spicy notes leaving a lasting impression.

For those seeking a more hearty meal, the ayam goreng is a must-try. The marinated chicken, deep-fried to golden perfection, is encased in a crispy batter that shatters with each bite, revealing tender, juicy meat within. The accompanying sambal adds a fiery kick, perfectly complementing the richness of the chicken.

For those seeking a comforting and soul-warming meal, the soto and bakso are excellent choices. The soto, a clear broth infused with the aromatic essence of spices, is generously filled with meat, vegetables, and a soft-boiled egg. Each spoonful is a symphony of flavors, providing a sense of warmth and satisfaction. The bakso, on the other hand, features succulent meatballs enveloped in a savory beef broth, accompanied by a medley of noodles and vegetables. The combination of textures and flavors is simply irresistible.

Beyond its culinary offerings, Warung Makan Muslim Taman Sari also impresses with its warm and welcoming ambiance. The warung's d√©cor is simple yet inviting, creating a comfortable and relaxed atmosphere. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring that each diner feels valued and appreciated.

Overall, Warung Makan Muslim Taman Sari is a culinary gem that deserves a spot on the itinerary of any traveler venturing to Tabanan. With its authentic Indonesian cuisine, warm hospitality, and affordable prices, the warung is a must-visit for those seeking a taste of true Balinese flavors.
